no Donadio -- Antiviral compounds of natural origin / Patricia Veiga -Crespo, Miquel Viñas and Tomás G. Villa -- New compounds with antibacterial activity -- Patricia Veiga-Crespo [and others] -- Use of antibiotic core structures to generate new and useful macrolide antibiotics / Prabhavathi Fernandes -- Antibiotics in the pipeline / Hyunjun Park and Michael Thomas -- Index -- Colour plate.  a"In this timely book, respected international experts summarize the most important research to provide an overview of the field [antibiotics]. Opening chapters define 'antibiotic', explain why we need new compounds, outline the applications of antibiotics, both old and new, and describe the producing microbes.  These are followed by chapters that cover antibiotic resistance, toxicity, overuse, new antimicrobial sources, new targets, novel technologies for antibiotic discover (e.g. silent gene clusters), lantibiotics, natural antivirals, new macrolide derivatives, and antibiotics in the pipeline.This book is essential reading for everyone working in antimicrobial research in academia, biotechnology companies, and the pharmaceutical industry and a recommended volume for all microbiology libraries"--Back cover.  a42 0aAntibiotics. 0aAntibioticsxAnalysis. 0aAntibiotics industry.1 aSánchez, Sergio Augusto,d1984-1 aDemain, A. L.q(Arnold L.),d1927-  aRM 267 A585 2015hUAHL-Bi0162035247574  aRM 267 A585 2015wLCc1i0162035247574lON_SHELFmUAHLTHSCp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu3/4/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n83009017bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/34519361